# Architecture Rules

## NestJS Backend — Hexagonal Architecture STRICT
```
domain/        → pure types, entities, ports (interfaces)
application/   → use cases, orchestration
infrastructure/ → NestJS modules, DB, HTTP, external services
```

### Domain Rules
- NO NestJS imports in domain
- NO database/IO in domain
- NO framework decorators in domain
- All side effects go through ports (interfaces)
- Domain is pure TypeScript

### Application Rules
- Use cases orchestrate domain logic
- Depend on domain ports, never on infrastructure
- One use case per file

### Infrastructure Rules
- Implements domain ports
- Contains NestJS modules, controllers, repositories
- All framework-specific code lives here

## AI System
1. Intent Generator (LLM) → parse user message to Intent
2. Intent Validator → check Intent is safe and valid
3. Action Resolver → map Intent to CMS action
4. LLM NEVER executes directly — always goes through validation

## Safety
- No direct DB access from LLM output
- No raw file writes from AI
- Validate all actions before execution
- Sanitize all outputs
- Limit file access scope
